The National Coronavirus command council will brief the media on the regulations relating to the COVID19 Level 3 restrictions following the announcements made by President Cyril Ramaphosa on Sunday evening. * Editor's note: This live event is expected to start at 2pm. JOHANNESBURG - Government says it will on Thursday afternoon finally lay bare all Level 3 lockdown regulations. Minister in the Presidency Jackson Mthembu says the much-awaited briefing will be addressed by, among others, cooperative governance minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma and her trade and industry counterpart, Ibrahim Patel. READ: Mthembu clarifies delay on lockdown regulations On Wednesday, The National Coronavirus Command Council and the social cluster briefing on socio-economic interventions for Level 3 restrictions were postponed. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced on Sunday that the whole of the country would move to Level 3 from next week.